en_692969_0	651 Brigade troops under the 65 Division of the Security Force Headquarters - Kilinochchi (SFHQ - KLN) considering the needs of the occasion, voluntarily offered assistance to a needy family for conduct of the funeral of their 13-year old son who accidentally died recently while riding a swing in the home compound in Iranamanathanagar, Ambapuram, Kilinochchi.
en_692969_1	At the request of the family, Major General Kumara Peiris, General Officer Commanding (GOC), 65 Division under the guidelines given by Major General Niyshshanka Ranawana, Commander, Security Forces - Kilinochchi (SF-KLN) provided the house of mourning with temporary marquees, chairs, cooking utensils, meals (on all two days) and other requirements.
en_692969_2	On the funeral day, sanitary facilities were put up near the house and facilitated villagers in Ambapuram to pay their last respects.
en_692969_3	Troops provided refreshments, packets of biscuits and cooked meals to all those who were attending as gestures of considerateness, sympathy, goodwill and reconciliation.
en_692969_4	In addition, Brigadier Ranjith Abeysinghe, Commander, 651 Brigade, together with several other Officers and Other Ranks attended the funeral in the nearby burial ground.
